Pushkara; each Dvipa is encircled by one of the seven oceans, viz. the
seas of Lava*n*a (salt-water), Ikshu (syrup), Sarpi*h* (butter), Dadhi
(sour milk), Dugdha (milk), Svâdhu (treacle), and Udaka (water), (Nand.)
The enumerations contained in the Vish*n*u-purâ*n*a and other works
differ on two or three points only from that given by Nand.--

